  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Why is magnesium glycinate better than other forms?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Magnesium glycinate (magnesium bound to the amino acid glycine) offers two distinct advantages over other forms. First, it has significantly higher bioavailability than magnesium oxide (which is only 4% absorbed) or magnesium citrate. The glycine amino acid acts as a transport carrier, facilitating absorption across the intestinal lining. Second, glycine itself has calming properties — it acts as an inhibitory neurotransmitter that binds to NMDA receptors in the brain, promoting relaxation and sleep. This dual benefit makes magnesium glycinate the preferred form for sleep, anxiety, and stress management. It is also the gentlest form on the digestive system, causing significantly fewer GI side effects (diarrhea, cramping) than citrate or oxide forms.' } },
