    <h2 id="why-glycinate">Why Magnesium Glycinate Is the Superior Form</h2>

    <p>Not all magnesium supplements are created equal. The form of magnesium — what the mineral is bound to — determines how much your body actually absorbs, how it affects your digestive system, and what secondary benefits it provides. Magnesium glycinate (magnesium chelated to the amino acid glycine) consistently outperforms other forms across these three critical dimensions, making it the preferred choice for practitioners who understand magnesium biochemistry.</p>

