        <p>Magnesium glycinate absorbs at 20-30% versus 4% for oxide. The chelated amino acid form uses active transport pathways rather than passive diffusion, delivering more magnesium per milligram consumed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Gentle on digestion</strong>
        <p>Unlike citrate and oxide forms that cause osmotic diarrhea, glycinate is absorbed through amino acid pathways with minimal unabsorbed magnesium reaching the colon. The gentlest form available.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Dual calming action</strong>
        <p>Magnesium activates GABA receptors for relaxation. Glycine independently promotes calming NMDA receptor activity. Together, they provide the strongest natural calming effect of any magnesium form.</p>
      </div>
